   <note>Reprint of Fain`s Case: John H. Fain v. The United States. Case summary notes: "The claimant mingles his own funds with those of another person to be invested in fifty-eight bales of cotton, which are taken under the `Abandoned or captured property act,` sold, and the net proceeds deposited in the treasury. The extent of the interest of each party is shown. The claimant alone brings suit for the whole amount of the net proceeds of the fifty-eight bales."</note>
